TOPIC 34:
APPLIED CHEMISTRY
DURATION:
12 Periods
GENERAL OBJECTIVE:
By the end of this topic the learner should be able to appreciate the importance and application of
chemistry in every day life.
SUB-TOPIC
SPECIFIC OBJECTIVE
CONTENT
The following processes should be used to
illustrate: -
- The chemical principles already covered in
the course.

industrial processes • Outline the application of
electrolysis in sodium
extraction
Describe how iron is extracted
by reduction
• Outline how copper is refined
by electrolysis.
Define an alloy.
State some common alloys and
give their composition.
Describe how sugar is
manufactured in an industry.

(particular reference to East Africa) availability
of raw materials, choice of site, social and
economic factors, health and pollution
problems, supply and demands.

Copper refining and uses of copper.

duralumin,

• Large scale extraction of sugar from sugar

STRATEGIES
Discuss the extraction sodium
- Highlight the application of
electrolysis in the process.
Discuss the extraction of iron.
Highlight the application of
reduction in the processes.
Discuss copper refining.
Highlight the application of

Discuss the definition of
alloy and the compositions of
the alloys that have been

processes should be encourages.

previous topics from Senior one to Senior four.
